# Always release after fixes

When you change Hue behavior, UI, config, or packaging in a way the installed app needs:

1. **Do not stop at local code** — finish by shipping an update.
2. Run **`npm run release`** from the repo root (bumps patch, builds, signs, pushes tag, publishes GitHub Release).
3. Tell the user the new version and that they can use Preferences → Advanced → **Check for updates**.

Applies after bug fixes, gesture/UX changes, prefs changes, and similar product work — not after docs-only or rule-only edits unless the user also asked for a release.
